      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the chicken and broth",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the {{chicken-thigh}}, {{carrot}}, {{celery}}, {{onion}}, {{garlic}}, {{thyme-fresh}}, {{bay-leaves}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{black-pepper}} to the slow cooker. Pour over the {{stock-chicken}}. Cook on low for 4 hours. Remove the chicken and shred the meat from the bones with two forks. Discard the skin and bones. Return the shredded meat to the pot. Remove the {{thyme-fresh}} sprigs and {{bay-leaves}}. Add the {{long-grain-rice}}, stir, and continue cooking on low for 1 hour, until the rice is tender. Add a squeeze of {{lemon}} juice to finish if using. Taste and adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "For next time, add rice in the last 60 minutes only. If this has already happened, the soup is still edible. It is closer to a congee in texture",
              "cause": "Rice added too early or cooked longer than 1 hour",
              "symptom": "Rice dissolved and soup has become thick porridge"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Season generously at the end. A squeeze of lemon juice also brightens a flat broth. Use good-quality liquid stock or homemade for this recipe",
              "cause": "Stock was diluted or low quality",
              "symptom": "Broth tastes thin and weak"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Switch to high and check after 20 minutes. Long-grain rice should cook in 60 minutes on low, but some cookers run cooler",
              "cause": "Slow cooker running cool, or rice variety needs longer",
              "symptom": "Rice still firm after 1 hour"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chicken and rice soup is a restorative dish for cold days, illness, and low-effort evenings. The slow cooker version requires nothing after the first ten minutes. The bone-in thighs produce a richer broth than boneless. Serve in deep bowls with crusty bread and a squeeze of lemon.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
